headlines.description: — Kevin Durant had 29 points and 10 rebounds, James Harden added a triple-double and the Brooklyn Nets extended their winning streak to four games with a 96-90 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant's 29, Harden's triple-double lead Nets past Pistons

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Orlando Magic

headlines.description: — In addition to Dejounte Murray shooting the 3-pointer better and scoring at a career-best clip, San Antonio Spurs coach Gregg Popovich said his point guard has shown marked improvement in his leadership abilities and knowing when to take games over.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spurs frustrate Magic with timely defense in 102-89 victory

headlines.description: — Bradley Beal scored 17 points, one of seven Washington players in double figures, and the Wizards routed the Memphis Grizzlies 115-87 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wizards have 7 in double figures, rout Grizzlies 115-87

headlines.description: — Darius Garland made a pair of free throws with 4.8 seconds remaining, and the Cleveland Cavaliers rallied to beat the Raptors 102-101 on Friday night, ending Toronto’s winning streak at five games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Garland hits go-ahead free throws, Cavs beat Raptors 102-101

events.name: New York Knicks at Milwaukee Bucks

headlines.description: — Julius Randle had 32 points and 12 rebounds, and the New York Knicks erased an early 21-point deficit and beat the Milwaukee Bucks 113-98 on Friday night.

— Paul George had 21 points and 11 rebounds, Reggie Jackson scored 14 of his 20 points in the second half, and the Los Angeles Clippers rallied from a 20-point deficit to beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 104-84 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers rally from 20 down to beat Timberwolves 104-84

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Jordan Poole scored 26 points, Stephen Curry had 19 and the Golden State Warriors routed the New Orleans Pelicans 126-85 on Friday night to improve to 7-1.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jordan Poole scores 26 points, Warriors rout Pelicans 126-85

events.name: Indiana Pacers at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — CJ McCollum scored 27 points, making five 3-pointers, and the Portland Trail Blazers rallied to beat the Indiana Pacers 110-106 on Friday night and snap a three-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCollum scores 27, leads Blazers past Pacers, 110-106

headlines.description: — Richaun Holmes had 23 points and a career-best 20 rebounds and the Sacramento Kings made a franchise-record 22 3-pointers in a 140-110 victory over the Charlotte Hornets on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings make 22 3s, Holmes star in 140-110 win over Hornets
